      {
        "id": "transformer_architecture",
        "title": "The Transformer: Putting It All Together",
        "content": "Key ideas:\n- No recurrence needed\n- Parallel processing\n- State-of-the-art results\n\nRNNs must wait for previous tokens before computing the next one (O(n) sequential steps). Transformers compute all attention in parallel — each token simultaneously attends to all others. This enables massive speedups and better scaling to long sequences.",
        "position": {
          "x": 9,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      }
    ],
    "quiz": {
      "id": "quiz-stage-3",
      "question": "RNNs process sequences token-by-token (slow). Transformers process all tokens in parallel. What enables this parallelization? (1) Self-attention (2) GPUs (3) Positional encoding.",
      "type": "multiple-choice",
      "options": [
        "Self-attention",
        "GPUs",
        "Positional encoding"
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "Self-attention",
